The paper deals with the fundamental limits of communication in scenarios where transmissions are very bursty and asynchronous, which are common in sensor networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with timing uncertainty and cost functions, which are relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses entropy as a measure of timing uncertainty, which is a concept from Machine Learning (cs.LG).
